snippet.textDisplay:
Neither Bron or AD are more valuable than the other. Bron spreads the floor, creates plays, and gets the whole team involved while also scoring when needed. AD locks down the post with his stifling defense, and helps carry the scoring load with LeBron.

Without AD, you lose a lot of points and a huge gap down low. Without LeBron, the team is stagnant and everyone plays for themselves.

snippet.textDisplay: Anthony Davis is a winner. Since his UK days leading them to national championship hes just been so special since day 1 in the league. He always gives 110% effort and has a basketball iq to match. He's a generational type player. And has been severely under appreciated for being drafted by Charlotte and spending 8 years there. Where they did absolutely nothing to put pieces around him and win games. Im just so blown away by how good this guy has been since college. I mean at UK he owned the world of college basketball and unlike Zion who gets all the hype and talk as being the best college player since durant. He actually led his team to a national championship and did it with ease. To me Anthony Davis is the best player to come to the league since LeBron James. Hands down!
